Take a look at the pins in the bottom of a cartridge before you buy it.  If the pins look like this, you do not have an adaptor:<br /><br />XXX<br />XXXX<br />XXX<br /><br />XXX<br />XXXX<br />XXX<br /><br />XXX<br />XXXX<br />XXX<br /><br />If the pins look like this (or oposite), you have an adaptor:<br /><br />XXXX<br />XXX<br />XXX<br /><br />XXXX<br />XXX<br />XXX<br /><br />XXXX<br />XXX<br />XXX<br /><br />The weight of the cart and the pins are the two determining factor.  I don't think that any other markings are for sure.  Buy a copy of stack up if you want to be sure you'll get one.  My understanding is every copy of stack up has the adaptor.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=231">sevast</a> — Tue Mar 21, 2006 5:08 pm</p><hr />
