<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1232&amp;p=10997#p10997"><![CDATA[
Well, I've managed to open two famicarts, but each time I broke 1 tab on the sides. It's actually not hard to get the top ones unlatched, just put a screwdriver in one of the openings on top, pry, and the latch nearest to the hole you stuck the screwdriver in will unlatch. But I broke one of the side ones each time. I was sort of sad. I'm thankfull I didn't break 2, or there'd be big problems. Those tabs are EVIL. I had to stand on my famicart to get it to latch again. I just have to work on opening the side tabs, because it's not easy to do without breaking it.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=138">Celius</a> — Sun Mar 19, 2006 9:28 pm</p><hr />
